00:00:21.516 --> 00:00:26.946 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:00:27.446 --> 00:00:31.176 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Hi, I'm Caroline
Cranfill and I'm a designer

00:00:31.176 --> 00:00:33.276 A:middle
and production manager
here at Apple.

00:00:33.936 --> 00:00:37.546 A:middle
Today, I'm excited to talk
to you about some principles

00:00:37.836 --> 00:00:39.446 A:middle
about inclusive design.

00:00:39.976 --> 00:00:43.776 A:middle
When you put so much hard work
and creativity into an app,

00:00:44.186 --> 00:00:46.576 A:middle
you really want it
to reach people.

00:00:47.226 --> 00:00:50.586 A:middle
But ultimately, everyone
will experience your app

00:00:50.906 --> 00:00:54.466 A:middle
in their own way and if you
think about the millions

00:00:54.466 --> 00:00:56.666 A:middle
of people who could
use your app,

00:00:56.966 --> 00:00:59.956 A:middle
you have to consider how
diverse their perspectives are.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:01:01.506 --> 00:01:05.176 A:middle
Some people are just learning
how to interact with technology.

00:01:07.126 --> 00:01:10.946 A:middle
Others are digital natives
who are completely comfortable

00:01:11.226 --> 00:01:12.846 A:middle
with the latest and greatest.

00:01:13.276 --> 00:01:16.906 A:middle
And there's some who are just
trying to get comfortable

00:01:16.906 --> 00:01:18.466 A:middle
with the new way to communicate.

00:01:19.986 --> 00:01:22.466 A:middle
And some will have
cultural backgrounds

00:01:22.466 --> 00:01:24.136 A:middle
that are very different
from yours.

00:01:24.646 --> 00:01:28.946 A:middle
And some will interact with your
app with assistive technology

00:01:29.176 --> 00:01:30.946 A:middle
like a Bluetooth
Braille Display.

00:01:32.326 --> 00:01:35.516 A:middle
So when you're trying to
ship an app, it always feels

00:01:35.516 --> 00:01:38.786 A:middle
like there isn't enough time and
there aren't enough resources

00:01:38.966 --> 00:01:41.856 A:middle
and it only gets worse the
closer you get to the end.

00:01:42.416 --> 00:01:45.726 A:middle
So that's why it's important to
plan to make your app inclusive

00:01:46.056 --> 00:01:48.656 A:middle
as early as possible in
the development cycle.

00:01:49.486 --> 00:01:52.896 A:middle
The problem is that early in
the cycle, everyone just wants

00:01:52.896 --> 00:01:55.506 A:middle
to talk about the cool
feature ideas they have.

00:01:56.096 --> 00:01:59.106 A:middle
So you need to convince your
team to do the right thing.

00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:02.796 A:middle
And here are some statistics
that will persuade them


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:02.796 A:middle
And here are some statistics
that will persuade them

00:02:03.006 --> 00:02:05.736 A:middle
to make inclusiveness
a high level feature.

00:02:06.836 --> 00:02:11.606 A:middle
Tim Cook recently announced
that 67 percent of Apple sales

00:02:11.856 --> 00:02:13.906 A:middle
in the second quarter
were international.

00:02:14.446 --> 00:02:17.166 A:middle
Your app needs to be
inclusive and flexible

00:02:17.166 --> 00:02:21.026 A:middle
to reach this huge market of
people with diverse backgrounds.

00:02:22.436 --> 00:02:29.046 A:middle
Worldwide, 285 million people
are blind or have low vision.

00:02:29.496 --> 00:02:32.076 A:middle
That's like half the
population of North America.

00:02:33.716 --> 00:02:38.556 A:middle
Over one billion people live
with some kind of disability.

00:02:39.086 --> 00:02:42.256 A:middle
That's one out of every
seven people on the planet.

00:02:43.266 --> 00:02:46.916 A:middle
Now disability and diversity
may not be the first things you

00:02:46.916 --> 00:02:49.616 A:middle
think about when you think
about user experience.

00:02:50.106 --> 00:02:53.196 A:middle
But these numbers make it
clear, these are the people

00:02:53.246 --> 00:02:57.396 A:middle
that use your app and creating
designs that work for them is

00:02:57.396 --> 00:02:59.506 A:middle
at the heart of the
user experience.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:03:00.646 --> 00:03:04.286 A:middle
So, how can you make
your apps more inclusive?

00:03:04.876 --> 00:03:08.376 A:middle
Fortunately, there are a
small number of key principles

00:03:08.666 --> 00:03:10.316 A:middle
that I have found to be helpful.

00:03:11.606 --> 00:03:14.286 A:middle
If you incorporate these
principles into your process,

00:03:14.656 --> 00:03:17.556 A:middle
you will have more informed
designs from the beginning.

00:03:17.976 --> 00:03:21.216 A:middle
And in the end, your app
will not only work better

00:03:21.216 --> 00:03:24.096 A:middle
for more people, but
you may also save time

00:03:24.096 --> 00:03:25.456 A:middle
on localization and QA.

00:03:26.576 --> 00:03:29.086 A:middle
So today, I'm going
to share some concepts

00:03:29.086 --> 00:03:32.366 A:middle
that I found eye opening and now
keep in mind when I'm designing.

00:03:33.356 --> 00:03:36.616 A:middle
I'll discuss how to use
typography to maintain hierarchy

00:03:36.616 --> 00:03:38.076 A:middle
in different localizations.

00:03:38.896 --> 00:03:42.016 A:middle
I'll show you why layouts
need to be dynamically built

00:03:42.276 --> 00:03:44.006 A:middle
to accommodate translation
lengths,

00:03:44.176 --> 00:03:46.216 A:middle
screen sizes and dynamic type.

00:03:46.216 --> 00:03:50.996 A:middle
And we'll discuss emotions
and legibility considerations

00:03:51.246 --> 00:03:53.076 A:middle
when making design
choices with color.

00:03:54.116 --> 00:03:56.986 A:middle
And we'll go over certain
cultural sensitivities

00:03:56.986 --> 00:03:57.966 A:middle
around iconography.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:04:04.376 --> 00:04:08.386 A:middle
So first, we'll talk about
the need impactful typography

00:04:08.386 --> 00:04:10.806 A:middle
for everyone regardless
of language.

00:04:11.426 --> 00:04:14.846 A:middle
Because the most fundamental
objective of app design is

00:04:14.846 --> 00:04:16.786 A:middle
to communicate information
clearly

00:04:16.956 --> 00:04:19.106 A:middle
and we largely do
that with typography.

00:04:19.736 --> 00:04:22.576 A:middle
So let's look at a quick
design exercise together.

00:04:23.326 --> 00:04:27.276 A:middle
One of the ways you know
what is most important is

00:04:27.276 --> 00:04:29.546 A:middle
by using basic typographic
treatments

00:04:29.706 --> 00:04:33.106 A:middle
and compositional elements to
give visual cues of hierarchy.

00:04:33.966 --> 00:04:37.486 A:middle
You can use extra space between
different pieces of information

00:04:38.836 --> 00:04:40.726 A:middle
or try different font sizes.

00:04:42.276 --> 00:04:45.636 A:middle
Or you can explore typographic
styles like font weights

00:04:46.726 --> 00:04:51.176 A:middle
or character styles like
capitalization or italics.

00:04:51.886 --> 00:04:55.546 A:middle
Or start adding color
and before you know it,

00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:57.236 A:middle
you have so many good options.

00:04:57.626 --> 00:05:00.736 A:middle
And at this stage, it's
an excellent opportunity


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:04:57.626 --> 00:05:00.736 A:middle
And at this stage, it's
an excellent opportunity

00:05:00.976 --> 00:05:05.156 A:middle
to preview your favorite options
in other languages you are going

00:05:05.156 --> 00:05:08.276 A:middle
to localize in because
you want all localizations

00:05:08.276 --> 00:05:11.326 A:middle
to have this same impact
as your original intention.

00:05:12.276 --> 00:05:15.546 A:middle
In this example, the hierarchy
isn't as strong in the title

00:05:15.546 --> 00:05:17.976 A:middle
and subtitle of the
Chinese localization

00:05:18.216 --> 00:05:21.346 A:middle
because the Chinese writing
system doesn't have the concept

00:05:21.516 --> 00:05:22.796 A:middle
of upper and lowercase.

00:05:23.036 --> 00:05:28.606 A:middle
In the second design, the title
additionally has a larger font

00:05:28.606 --> 00:05:30.836 A:middle
size and color from the subtitle

00:05:31.076 --> 00:05:33.696 A:middle
which helps maintain a
clear hierarchy in Chinese.

00:05:34.226 --> 00:05:36.536 A:middle
So out of my two favorites,

00:05:36.536 --> 00:05:39.856 A:middle
this second design is
the most robust choice

00:05:40.116 --> 00:05:41.456 A:middle
because it creates hierarchy

00:05:41.456 --> 00:05:43.626 A:middle
through using two
typographic treatments,

00:05:43.916 --> 00:05:47.466 A:middle
both localizations can support,
which is font size and color.

00:05:47.886 --> 00:05:51.556 A:middle
I've found that once a design
is going to be translated

00:05:51.556 --> 00:05:54.716 A:middle
into multiple languages,
having two to three levels

00:05:54.716 --> 00:05:57.286 A:middle
of change will be
more inclusive just

00:05:57.286 --> 00:06:00.216 A:middle
in case a treatment isn't
applicable in certain languages.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:57.286 --> 00:06:00.216 A:middle
in case a treatment isn't
applicable in certain languages.

00:06:01.036 --> 00:06:03.396 A:middle
And sometimes, designing
with constraints

00:06:03.396 --> 00:06:06.166 A:middle
like these can help come up
with a better end solution

00:06:06.166 --> 00:06:06.876 A:middle
for everyone.

00:06:08.156 --> 00:06:10.156 A:middle
Here's another example
at Airbnb.

00:06:10.156 --> 00:06:15.006 A:middle
They use font size, color, and
extra space between information

00:06:15.236 --> 00:06:17.806 A:middle
to maintain hierarchy
across localizations.

00:06:18.306 --> 00:06:22.766 A:middle
And so now for you to have
more background knowledge

00:06:22.766 --> 00:06:25.436 A:middle
and feel informed to
design for other languages,

00:06:25.436 --> 00:06:29.086 A:middle
I want to dive a little
deeper about a few topics.

00:06:30.506 --> 00:06:33.466 A:middle
First, it's important to
remember that around the world,

00:06:33.506 --> 00:06:36.616 A:middle
we speak different languages
and use different alphabets.

00:06:37.096 --> 00:06:39.826 A:middle
So, I want to introduce
you to some writing systems

00:06:39.906 --> 00:06:41.436 A:middle
that you may not
be familiar with

00:06:41.896 --> 00:06:44.946 A:middle
and how hierarchy can be
lost if you aren't aware

00:06:44.946 --> 00:06:46.116 A:middle
of their typographic support.

00:06:47.396 --> 00:06:50.486 A:middle
So everyone here knows this
writing system called Latin.

00:06:51.356 --> 00:06:53.286 A:middle
But you may not be
familiar with characters

00:06:53.286 --> 00:06:56.056 A:middle
in the extended Latin
character set such as these.

00:06:56.506 --> 00:06:58.716 A:middle
And you really might
not be familiar

00:06:58.986 --> 00:07:01.476 A:middle
with all ten writing
systems that are used


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:06:58.986 --> 00:07:01.476 A:middle
with all ten writing
systems that are used

00:07:01.476 --> 00:07:04.906 A:middle
in over forty languages or
localizations that we ship.

00:07:05.386 --> 00:07:09.786 A:middle
A few typographic things that
you might not be aware of is

00:07:09.786 --> 00:07:12.846 A:middle
that some writing systems do
not have the concept of upper

00:07:12.936 --> 00:07:14.726 A:middle
and lowercase as I
mentioned earlier.

00:07:16.166 --> 00:07:20.176 A:middle
Also, the same subset does
not have an italic appearance

00:07:20.606 --> 00:07:23.306 A:middle
and it's not in good
practice to force a slant

00:07:23.306 --> 00:07:24.576 A:middle
on these writing systems.

00:07:26.176 --> 00:07:29.396 A:middle
So now you need to know
that different fonts

00:07:29.426 --> 00:07:32.306 A:middle
for these writing systems
have different numbers

00:07:32.306 --> 00:07:33.286 A:middle
of font weights.

00:07:34.826 --> 00:07:36.606 A:middle
Currently these are
the font weights

00:07:36.606 --> 00:07:39.256 A:middle
in the system font,
San Francisco.

00:07:39.256 --> 00:07:43.616 A:middle
But you can see that the system
fonts for all writing systems

00:07:43.616 --> 00:07:46.826 A:middle
at the moment do not have the
same number of font weights.

00:07:47.836 --> 00:07:52.156 A:middle
So this means your designs using
extreme weights may fall back

00:07:52.156 --> 00:07:52.966 A:middle
to the reduced set.

00:07:52.966 --> 00:07:55.336 A:middle
And this can be unexpected

00:07:55.336 --> 00:07:57.496 A:middle
and sometimes lose
hierarchy or emphasis.

00:07:57.706 --> 00:08:01.506 A:middle
In the next consideration,
I would like to talk


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:57.706 --> 00:08:01.506 A:middle
In the next consideration,
I would like to talk

00:08:01.506 --> 00:08:05.306 A:middle
about is using larger text sizes
because they are more universal

00:08:05.306 --> 00:08:07.776 A:middle
between languages and
user capabilities.

00:08:08.396 --> 00:08:09.646 A:middle
So let's start with
a good question

00:08:09.646 --> 00:08:11.056 A:middle
which is, "What is too small?"

00:08:12.666 --> 00:08:15.516 A:middle
Maybe everyone here can
see this bottom letter

00:08:15.516 --> 00:08:16.656 A:middle
on this enormous screen.

00:08:16.986 --> 00:08:19.996 A:middle
But on a smaller device,
it'll be too hard to read.

00:08:20.646 --> 00:08:22.766 A:middle
Legibility is really
going to depend

00:08:22.766 --> 00:08:24.586 A:middle
on what device you are targeting

00:08:24.866 --> 00:08:27.246 A:middle
because the standard viewing
distances are different.

00:08:27.936 --> 00:08:30.676 A:middle
But, even if the
letters are legible,

00:08:30.816 --> 00:08:33.716 A:middle
it doesn't mean it's going to
be good for reading content.

00:08:34.546 --> 00:08:37.366 A:middle
Let's look at a non-Latin
writing system like Chinese.

00:08:38.785 --> 00:08:41.535 A:middle
It gets harder to read
at a higher number

00:08:41.655 --> 00:08:45.816 A:middle
because rendering dense writing
systems too small can reduce the

00:08:45.816 --> 00:08:47.156 A:middle
clarity of letter forms.

00:08:47.686 --> 00:08:50.236 A:middle
The meaning can be
misconstrued or lost

00:08:50.236 --> 00:08:51.856 A:middle
because the strokes
blend together.

00:08:52.436 --> 00:08:57.156 A:middle
You want people to read their
content easily and effortlessly.

00:08:57.596 --> 00:09:01.206 A:middle
So leaning toward larger font
sizes will make the content more


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:08:57.596 --> 00:09:01.206 A:middle
So leaning toward larger font
sizes will make the content more

00:09:01.206 --> 00:09:02.346 A:middle
readable for everyone.

00:09:02.916 --> 00:09:06.516 A:middle
Now one more thing
about typography.

00:09:07.126 --> 00:09:10.386 A:middle
Some writing systems are
considered to be tall

00:09:10.626 --> 00:09:12.616 A:middle
because they have
tall letter forms.

00:09:14.116 --> 00:09:16.736 A:middle
As you might have noticed in
the writing system overview,

00:09:16.736 --> 00:09:19.586 A:middle
some of the examples
have extra marks

00:09:19.636 --> 00:09:20.936 A:middle
that we don't use in English.

00:09:21.356 --> 00:09:24.646 A:middle
These are call diacritics,
vowel marks, or tone marks

00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:27.406 A:middle
and sometimes they're
extremely high or low.

00:09:28.376 --> 00:09:31.956 A:middle
For example, in this Thai font
it can have ascenders much

00:09:32.036 --> 00:09:33.616 A:middle
higher than Latin characters.

00:09:35.476 --> 00:09:37.986 A:middle
And in these Arabic
and Hindi fonts,

00:09:38.236 --> 00:09:41.426 A:middle
they have descenders much
lower than Latin characters.

00:09:43.146 --> 00:09:45.046 A:middle
And you should also be aware

00:09:45.276 --> 00:09:47.416 A:middle
that in some code
implementations,

00:09:47.736 --> 00:09:50.566 A:middle
characters that draw
outside those ascender

00:09:50.566 --> 00:09:52.876 A:middle
and descender boundaries
of a font

00:09:52.876 --> 00:09:55.456 A:middle
and text views can
be cut off if clip

00:09:55.486 --> 00:09:57.316 A:middle
to bounds is true for the label.

00:09:57.616 --> 00:10:00.976 A:middle
This should be off,
because this is bad.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:09:57.616 --> 00:10:00.976 A:middle
This should be off,
because this is bad.

00:10:01.586 --> 00:10:04.916 A:middle
Missing marks can change the
meaning of the word entirely.

00:10:06.276 --> 00:10:08.736 A:middle
So, also in design comps,

00:10:08.736 --> 00:10:11.646 A:middle
you should avoid assuming
fixed heights for texts

00:10:11.946 --> 00:10:13.956 A:middle
because the letter
form is going to vary

00:10:13.956 --> 00:10:15.136 A:middle
in different writing systems.

00:10:16.446 --> 00:10:19.386 A:middle
So you might be thinking how
does this affect my layouts?

00:10:19.636 --> 00:10:21.226 A:middle
So let me show you
a quick example

00:10:21.226 --> 00:10:23.496 A:middle
of how labels will
adjust automatically

00:10:23.856 --> 00:10:25.676 A:middle
for these tall writing
systems and code.

00:10:27.276 --> 00:10:29.306 A:middle
If you look at this
composition consisting

00:10:29.306 --> 00:10:32.326 A:middle
of three separate
Latin text-size labels,

00:10:32.846 --> 00:10:35.756 A:middle
and you can see in a tall
writing system it requires a

00:10:35.756 --> 00:10:38.096 A:middle
larger line height
to avoid clipping.

00:10:38.726 --> 00:10:40.236 A:middle
And here they are, side by side.

00:10:40.466 --> 00:10:44.536 A:middle
And you can see that Thai text
is longer and it's been allowed

00:10:44.536 --> 00:10:45.916 A:middle
to expand appropriately.

00:10:46.316 --> 00:10:49.546 A:middle
And it's important that you
don't restrict the height

00:10:49.546 --> 00:10:52.066 A:middle
of the view so this
expansion can happen

00:10:52.536 --> 00:10:55.406 A:middle
because letter forms could
overlap or be illegible.

00:10:55.956 --> 00:10:58.966 A:middle
And later, we'll explain how to
make further make these spaces

00:10:58.966 --> 00:11:01.346 A:middle
between labels increase
dynamically


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:10:58.966 --> 00:11:01.346 A:middle
between labels increase
dynamically

00:11:01.346 --> 00:11:02.836 A:middle
to accommodate dynamic type.

00:11:04.026 --> 00:11:07.956 A:middle
So some things to remember
about typography that you need

00:11:07.956 --> 00:11:11.996 A:middle
to make sure designs will retain
the same meaningful purpose

00:11:11.996 --> 00:11:14.786 A:middle
in other languages by
preserving hierarchy,

00:11:15.086 --> 00:11:18.756 A:middle
by choosing universal character
styles, or by having two

00:11:18.756 --> 00:11:22.026 A:middle
to three levels of change
in case one isn't applicable

00:11:22.026 --> 00:11:23.306 A:middle
in one of the localizations.

00:11:25.116 --> 00:11:28.366 A:middle
Use font sizes that will
be easy to read across all

00:11:28.366 --> 00:11:31.686 A:middle
of your localizations and
capabilities of the people

00:11:31.686 --> 00:11:34.006 A:middle
who will use your app.

00:11:34.006 --> 00:11:37.636 A:middle
And don't restrict drawing of
views to their bounding boxes.

00:11:38.446 --> 00:11:40.866 A:middle
So now we've looked at a
little bit of typography.

00:11:41.096 --> 00:11:44.316 A:middle
For more information about
typography, be sure to check

00:11:44.316 --> 00:11:47.266 A:middle
out my friend Antonio's
session tomorrow morning called

00:11:47.266 --> 00:11:49.966 A:middle
Typography and Fonts
for even more details

00:11:49.966 --> 00:11:52.626 A:middle
on typographic treatments
and layout considerations.

00:11:53.726 --> 00:11:55.696 A:middle
But now, let's talk
about dynamic layouts.

00:11:56.396 --> 00:12:01.506 A:middle
We've talked about the
appearance of words from all


